did.unittitle: Preliminary Guide to the Washington State University Office of the President Records
did.abstract: Administrative and financial files related to the WSU President's Office from 1993-1998, in which Sam Smith was the presiding president.

bioghist.p: The president is the chief executive officer of the multi-campus Washington State University system and reports to a 10-member Board of Regents.

As the University’s leader, the president collaborates with a wide range of internal and external stakeholders to define the vision and set the direction for the institution. As the champion of its reputation, the president articulates the strategic goals and messages of the University in order to build broad support for and ownership of WSU’s aspirations among its many constituents, including faculty, staff, students, alumni, the Board of Regents, the WSU Foundation, local communities, government, business, and industry leaders statewide, the media, and the general public. Samuel (Sam) H. Smith was selected by the Board of Regents on March 7, 1985, to serve as the institution’s 8th president. He took office at age 45 on July 1, 1985, and served for 15 years.

scopecontent.p: Mostly administrative and financial files related to the WSU's Presidential Office during Sam Smith's time as president from 1993-1998.

arrangement.p: This is an unprocessed collection. Any arrangement reflects either a pre-existing order from the records' creators or previous custodians, or preliminary sorting performed by staff.

All boxes contain administrative files and correspondence related to the WSU President's Office. Boxes 1-9 contain files from 1993 and are organized by alphabet and subject matter. Boxes 10-17 contain files from 1994 and are filed by alphabet and subject order. Boxes 18-24 contain files from 1995-1998 and are filed by alphabet, date, and subject order.

accessrestrict.p: This collection is open and available for research use.

acqinfo.p: This material was transferred to WSU Libraries' MASC by Linda Commons of the President's Office on December 29, 2000 and retained as UA2000-41.
